<h2>River Description</h2>
<p>
Johnnies Creek is the classic class IV-IV+ creek in Alabama. The lower section from Canyon Rim
Road (CR 275) to the Little River is the most frequently run creek in Little River Canyon. It
runs more often then the other canyon creeks and seems to be everyone&#39;s favorite. It is solid
class IV-IV+ creeking with one class V and plenty of undercuts and sieves spread throughout the
run. It&#39;s continuous from start to finish, but its length and easy shuttle make multiple runs
per day the norm. The rapids are difficult to scout, and having someone take you down the first
time is a blessing. All rapids are runnable, although Gorilla Constrictor is often walked.
Several injuries have occurred here.
</p> <br>
<div style='clear:both'>
<div><b>StreamTeam Status: </b>Not Verified</div>
